  <section class="section"><div class="wrap narrow">
    <h2>Hestan in LA — Anaheim-factory proximity changes the service math</h2>
    <p>Most LA luxury-stove households don't think about parts-channel geography until they need a part and learn the stove will be down for 5-10 days waiting on Madison, Greenwood, or Blandon shipment. Hestan's Meyer Anaheim factory changes that math — parts ship 1-3 days to LA-authorized service on common components, which translates to typical 48-72 hour return-to-service on straightforward repairs vs 5-10+ days on out-of-state luxury brands. The practical value shows up during holidays and events: a Hestan Pro Series with a failed igniter on the Tuesday before Thanksgiving is back in service Friday morning, where the same failure on a Viking or Wolf often pushes into the following week.</p>
    <p>Hestan's LA install base concentrates in geographies where the Anaheim advantage is most visible. Orange County custom kitchens — Newport Coast, Corona del Mar, Laguna Beach, Newport Beach, Irvine — sit closest to the Anaheim factory and often see 24-48 hour parts. LA-side install concentration: Bel Air + Beverly Hills ultra-luxury remodels specifying Bordeaux or Matte color program; Pacific Palisades + Brentwood architectural kitchens; Hancock Park heritage homes with Matte Black Pro Series; Manhattan Beach + Palos Verdes coastal luxury. Hestan Cue smart integration is more common in chef-owned or tech-professional households that actively use the Cue app for sous-vide and precision-cook recipes. Our service approach respects finish integrity on color-matched units and supports Cue firmware / connectivity diagnostics as part of standard service.</p>
  </div></section>

  <section class="section alt"><div class="wrap">
    <h2>Hestan stove failures our techs see most often in LA</h2>
    <div class="fail-block"><h3>Burner no-light — orifice / spark / thermocouple</h3><p>Standard pro-range diagnostic. Orifice $180–$280 per burner on LP/NG mismatch; spark module $260–$380; thermocouple $220–$320. Anaheim parts 1-3 day lead.</p></div>
    <div class="fail-block"><h3>Hestan Cue Bluetooth connectivity</h3><p>Pan-recognition + firmware verification first. Cue-compatible Bluetooth module $280–$420 when hardware-side failure confirmed.</p></div>
    <div class="fail-block"><h3>Oven temperature drift</h3><p>Sensor drift at 5-8 years. Sensor $220–$320; control board $460–$660 when digital control is the fault source.</p></div>
    <div class="fail-block"><h3>Convection fan motor (dual-fuel electric oven)</h3><p>Motor swap $340–$500. Anaheim parts channel 1-3 day.</p></div>
    <div class="fail-block"><h3>Induction coil (induction variants)</h3><p>Coil swap $320–$480 per zone; induction-top control board $480–$660.</p></div>
    <div class="fail-block"><h3>Oven igniter glow-but-no-heat</h3><p>Igniter resistance out-of-spec. Swap $260–$380 on Hestan pro-range.</p></div>
  </div></section>

